        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 1:46PM CDT by NWS Nashville TN</headline>
        <description>At 146 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Clarksville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Palmyra, Cunningham, and Woodlawn.

This includes Interstate 24 between mile markers 1 and 13.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for Middle
Tennessee.</instruction>
